n = 100
m_0 = 7
sigma_0 = 8

X = np.random.normal(m_0, sigma_0, size=n)# 
W = (np.mean(X) - m_0) / np.sqrt(np.var(X, ddof=1) / n)# 
P = 2 * min(sts.t.cdf(W, df=n - 1), 1 - sts.t.cdf(W, df=n - 1) ) # p no 
wl, pl = sts.ttest_1samp(X, m_0, axis = 0, nan_policy='propagate')# p  ttest_1samp
print ("P  ttest_1samp", pl)
print ("P  ", P)
print ("    alpha < ", P)

n = 90
m_0 = 7
sigma_0 = 8
side = False

X = np.random.normal(m_0, sigma_0, size=n)# 
S = np.std(X)

V = np.var(X, ddof=1) / ((sigma_0 ** 2) / (n - 1))# 
if(S > sigma_0):
    P = sts.chi(n-1).cdf(V)
else:
    P = 1 - sts.chi(n-1).cdf(V)
print ("    alpha < ", P)

    #

N = [30, 60, 120]    #   
m0 = 7
sigma_0 = 8
alpha = 0.05

colors = ['#FFA500', '#C71585', '#4682B4']
for n in N:
    col = random.choice(colors)
    colors.remove(col)
    
    X = np.random.normal(m0, sigma_0, n)    #  
    st = sts.norm.ppf(1 - alpha)    #  
    
    spam = np.linspace(6, 14, 200)      #      
    M = 1 - sts.norm(spam, sigma_0 / np.sqrt(n)).cdf(st * sigma_0 / np.sqrt(n) + m0)    # 

    plt.plot(spam, M, label=f'n={n}', color=col)
    print(f" n={n}   - ({round(st, 5)}, inf)")
plt.grid()
plt.axhline(y=alpha, color='black', linestyle='dotted', label='alpha=0.05')     #  
plt.plot([st, st, 6, 14], [1, 0, 0, 0], '-o', label=' ', color='#800000')
plt.legend(loc='best')
plt.xlabel('malt')
plt.ylabel('')
plt.show()
